text: Katerina Nikoloska (born 30 December 1990) is an Macedonia judoka. The first Olympic judoka to represent Macedonia, she competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the women's 63 kg, where she was eliminated by Büşra Katipoğlu in the first round. ==References== Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Macedonian female judoka Category:Olympic judoka of North Macedonia Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:European Games competitors for North Macedonia Category:Judoka at the 2015 European Games
